                                         'child Timothy, according to the '
                                         'prophecies which were given to you '
                                         'before, that by them you may wage '
                                         'the good warfare;\n'
                                         'holding faith and a good conscience; '
                                         'which some having thrust away made a '
                                         'shipwreck concerning the faith;\n'
                                         'of whom are Hymenaeus and Alexander; '
                                         'whom I delivered to Satan, that they '
                                         'might be taught not to blaspheme.\n'
                                         'Let as many as are bondservants '
                                         'under the yoke count their own '
                                         'masters worthy of all honor, that '
                                         'the name of God and the doctrine not '
                                         'be blasphemed.\n'
