                                         'who is the blessed and only Ruler, '
                                         'the King of kings, and Lord of '
                                         'lords;\n'
                                         'who alone has immortality, dwelling '
                                         'in unapproachable light; whom no man '
                                         'has seen, nor can see: to whom be '
                                         'honor and eternal power. Amen.\n'
                                         'Charge those who are rich in this '
                                         'present world that they not be '
                                         'haughty, nor have their hope set on '
                                         'the uncertainty of riches, but on '
                                         'the living God, who richly provides '
                                         'us with everything to enjoy;\n'
