                                         'evil to me. The Lord will repay him '
                                         'according to his deeds,\n'
                                         'of whom you also must beware; for he '
                                         'greatly opposed our words.\n'
                                         'At my first defense, no one came to '
                                         'help me, but all left me. May it not '
                                         'be held against them.\n'
                                         'But the Lord stood by me, and '
                                         'strengthened me, that through me the '
                                         'message might be fully proclaimed, '
                                         'and that all the Gentiles might '
                                         'hear; and I was delivered out of the '
                                         'mouth of the lion.\n'
                                         'And the Lord will deliver me from '
                                         'every evil work, and will preserve '
                                         'me for his heavenly Kingdom; to whom '
                                         'be the glory forever and ever. '
                                         'Amen.\n'
                                         'Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the '
