                                      'encouraged in you, each of us by the '
                                      "other's faith, both yours and mine.\n"
                                      "Now I don't desire to have you unaware, "
                                      'brothers, that I often planned to come '
                                      'to you, and was hindered so far, that I '
                                      'might have some fruit among you also, '
                                      'even as among the rest of the '
                                      'Gentiles.\n'
                                      'I am debtor both to Greeks and to '
                                      'foreigners, both to the wise and to the '
                                      'foolish.\n'
                                      'So, as much as is in me, I am eager to '
                                      'preach the Good News to you also who '
                                      'are in Rome.\n'
                                      'For I am not ashamed of the Good News '
