                                        'Ashkelon,\n'
                                        'lest the daughters of the Philistines '
                                        'rejoice,\n'
                                        'lest the daughters of the '
                                        'uncircumcised triumph.\n'
                                        'You mountains of Gilboa,\n'
                                        'let there be no dew or rain on you, '
                                        'and no fields of offerings;\n'
                                        'For there the shield of the mighty '
                                        'was defiled and cast away,\n'
                                        'The shield of Saul was not anointed '
                                        'with oil.\n'
                                        'From the blood of the slain,\n'
                                        'from the fat of the mighty,\n'
                                        "Jonathan's bow didn't turn back.\n"
                                        "Saul's sword didn't return empty.\n"
                                        'Saul and Jonathan were lovely and '
                                        'pleasant in their lives.\n'
                                        'In their death, they were not '
                                        'divided.\n'
                                        'They were swifter than eagles.\n'
                                        'They were stronger than lions.\n'
                                        'You daughters of Israel, weep over '
                                        'Saul,\n'
                                        'who clothed you delicately in '
                                        'scarlet,\n'
                                        'who put ornaments of gold on your '
                                        'clothing.\n'
                                        'How the mighty have fallen in the '
                                        'middle of the battle!\n'
                                        'Jonathan was slain on your high '
                                        'places.\n'
                                        'I am distressed for you, my brother '
                                        'Jonathan.\n'
                                        'You have been very pleasant to me.\n'
                                        'Your love to me was wonderful,\n'
                                        'passing the love of women.\n'
                                        'How the mighty have fallen,\n'
                                        'and the weapons of war have '
                                        "perished!'\n"
                                        "Again Yahweh's anger burned against "
                                        'Israel, and he moved David against '
                                        "them, saying, 'Go, count Israel and "
                                        "Judah.'\n"
                                        'The king said to Joab the captain of '
                                        "the army, who was with him, 'Now go "
                                        'back and forth through all the tribes '
                                        'of Israel, from Dan even to '
                                        'Beersheba, and count the people, that '
                                        "I may know the sum of the people.'\n"
                                        "Joab said to the king, 'Now may "
                                        'Yahweh your God add to the people, '
                                        'however many they may be, one hundred '
                                        'times; and may the eyes of my lord '
                                        'the king see it. But why does my lord '
                                        "the king delight in this thing?'\n"
