                                           'the commandment of Yahweh, and '
                                           'were presumptuous, and went up '
                                           'into the hill country.\n'
                                           'The Amorites, who lived in that '
                                           'hill country, came out against '
                                           'you, and chased you, as bees do, '
                                           'and beat you down in Seir, even to '
                                           'Hormah.\n'
                                           'You returned and wept before '
                                           "Yahweh; but Yahweh didn't listen "
                                           'to your voice, nor turn his ear to '
                                           'you.\n'
                                           'So you stayed in Kadesh many days, '
                                           'according to the days that you '
                                           'remained.\n'
                                           'Moses went up from the plains of '
                                           'Moab to Mount Nebo, to the top of '
                                           'Pisgah, that is over against '
                                           'Jericho. Yahweh showed him all the '
                                           'land of Gilead, to Dan,\n'
