                                      'the people multiplied, and grew very '
                                      'mighty.\n'
                                      'Because the midwives feared God, he '
                                      'gave them families.\n'
                                      'Pharaoh commanded all his people, '
                                      "saying, 'You shall cast every son who "
                                      'is born into the river, and every '
                                      "daughter you shall save alive.'\n"
                                      'Yahweh spoke to Moses, saying,\n'
                                      "'On the first day of the first month "
                                      'you shall raise up the tabernacle of '
                                      'the Tent of Meeting.\n'
                                      'You shall put the ark of the testimony '
                                      'in it, and you shall screen the ark '
                                      'with the veil.\n'
                                      'You shall bring in the table, and set '
                                      'in order the things that are on it. You '
                                      'shall bring in the lamp stand, and '
                                      'light its lamps.\n'
                                      'You shall set the golden altar for '
                                      'incense before the ark of the '
                                      'testimony, and put the screen of the '
                                      'door to the tabernacle.\n'
                                      "'You shall set the altar of burnt "
                                      'offering before the door of the '
                                      'tabernacle of the Tent of Meeting.\n'
                                      'You shall set the basin between the '
                                      'Tent of Meeting and the altar, and '
                                      'shall put water therein.\n'
                                      'You shall set up the court around it, '
                                      'and hang up the screen of the gate of '
                                      'the court.\n'
                                      "'You shall take the anointing oil, and "
                                      'anoint the tabernacle, and all that is '
                                      'in it, and shall make it holy, and all '
                                      'its furniture: and it will be holy.\n'
                                      'You shall anoint the altar of burnt '
                                      'offering, with all its vessels, and '
                                      'sanctify the altar: and the altar will '
                                      'be most holy.\n'
                                      'You shall anoint the basin and its '
                                      'base, and sanctify it.\n'
                                      "'You shall bring Aaron and his sons to "
                                      'the door of the Tent of Meeting, and '
                                      'shall wash them with water.\n'
                                      'You shall put on Aaron the holy '
                                      'garments; and you shall anoint him, and '
                                      'sanctify him, that he may minister to '
                                      "me in the priest's office.\n"
                                      'You shall bring his sons, and put coats '
                                      'on them.\n'
                                      'You shall anoint them, as you anointed '
                                      'their father, that they may minister to '
                                      "me in the priest's office. Their "
                                      'anointing shall be to them for an '
                                      'everlasting priesthood throughout their '
                                      "generations.'\n"
                                      'Moses did so. According to all that '
                                      'Yahweh commanded him, so he did.\n'
                                      'In the first month in the second year, '
                                      'on the first day of the month, the '
                                      'tabernacle was raised up.\n'
                                      'Moses raised up the tabernacle, and '
                                      'laid its sockets, and set up its '
                                      'boards, and put in its bars, and raised '
                                      'up its pillars.\n'
                                      'He spread the covering over the tent, '
                                      'and put the roof of the tabernacle '
                                      'above on it, as Yahweh commanded '
                                      'Moses.\n'
                                      'He took and put the testimony into the '
                                      'ark, and set the poles on the ark, and '
                                      'put the mercy seat above on the ark.\n'
                                      'He brought the ark into the tabernacle, '
                                      'and set up the veil of the screen, and '
                                      'screened the ark of the testimony, as '
                                      'Yahweh commanded Moses.\n'
                                      'He put the table in the Tent of '
                                      'Meeting, on the side of the tabernacle '
                                      'northward, outside of the veil.\n'
                                      'He set the bread in order on it before '
                                      'Yahweh, as Yahweh commanded Moses.\n'
                                      'He put the lamp stand in the Tent of '
                                      'Meeting, opposite the table, on the '
                                      'side of the tabernacle southward.\n'
                                      'He lit the lamps before Yahweh, as '
                                      'Yahweh commanded Moses.\n'
                                      'He put the golden altar in the Tent of '
                                      'Meeting before the veil;\n'
                                      'and he burned incense of sweet spices '
                                      'on it, as Yahweh commanded Moses.\n'
                                      'He put up the screen of the door to the '
                                      'tabernacle.\n'
                                      'He set the altar of burnt offering at '
                                      'the door of the tabernacle of the Tent '
                                      'of Meeting, and offered on it the burnt '
                                      'offering and the meal offering, as '
                                      'Yahweh commanded Moses.\n'
                                      'He set the basin between the Tent of '
                                      'Meeting and the altar, and put water '
                                      'therein, with which to wash.\n'
                                      'Moses, Aaron, and his sons washed their '
                                      'hands and their feet there.\n'
                                      'When they went into the Tent of '
                                      'Meeting, and when they came near to the '
                                      'altar, they washed, as Yahweh commanded '
                                      'Moses.\n'
                                      'He raised up the court around the '
                                      'tabernacle and the altar, and set up '
                                      'the screen of the gate of the court. So '
                                      'Moses finished the work.\n'
                                      'Then the cloud covered the Tent of '
                                      "Meeting, and Yahweh's glory filled the "
                                      'tabernacle.\n'
                                      "Moses wasn't able to enter into the "
                                      'Tent of Meeting, because the cloud '
                                      "stayed on it, and Yahweh's glory filled "
                                      'the tabernacle.\n'
                                      'When the cloud was taken up from over '
                                      'the tabernacle, the children of Israel '
