                                        "said to me, 'Behold, I have put my "
                                        'words in your mouth.\n'
                                        'Behold, I have today set you over the '
                                        'nations and over the kingdoms, to '
                                        'uproot and to tear down, to destroy '
                                        'and to overthrow, to build and to '
                                        "plant.'\n"
                                        "Moreover Yahweh's word came to me, "
                                        "saying, 'Jeremiah, what do you see?'\n"
                                        "I said, 'I see a branch of an almond "
                                        "tree.'\n"
                                        "Then Yahweh said to me, 'You have "
                                        'seen well; for I watch over my word '
                                        "to perform it.'\n"
                                        "Yahweh's word came to me the second "
                                        "time, saying, 'What do you see?'\n"
                                        "I said, 'I see a boiling cauldron; "
                                        'and it is tipping away from the '
