                                      'Canaanites and the Perizzites into '
                                      'their hand. They struck ten thousand '
                                      'men in Bezek.\n'
                                      'They found Adoni-Bezek in Bezek, and '
                                      'they fought against him. They struck '
                                      'the Canaanites and the Perizzites.\n'
                                      'But Adoni-Bezek fled. They pursued him, '
                                      'caught him, and cut off his thumbs and '
                                      'his big toes.\n'
                                      "Adoni-Bezek said, 'Seventy kings, "
                                      'having their thumbs and their big toes '
                                      'cut off, scavenged under my table. As I '
                                      "have done, so God has done to me.' They "
                                      'brought him to Jerusalem, and he died '
                                      'there.\n'
                                      'The children of Judah fought against '
                                      'Jerusalem, took it, struck it with the '
                                      'edge of the sword, and set the city on '
                                      'fire.\n'
                                      'After that, the children of Judah went '
                                      'down to fight against the Canaanites '
                                      'who lived in the hill country, and in '
                                      'the South, and in the lowland.\n'
                                      'Judah went against the Canaanites who '
                                      'lived in Hebron. (The name of Hebron '
                                      'before that was Kiriath Arba.) They '
                                      'struck Sheshai, Ahiman, and Talmai.\n'
                                      'From there he went against the '
                                      'inhabitants of Debir. (The name of '
                                      'Debir before that was Kiriath Sepher.)\n'
                                      "Caleb said, 'I will give Achsah my "
                                      'daughter as wife to the man who strikes '
                                      "Kiriath Sepher, and takes it.'\n"
                                      "Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb's "
                                      'younger brother, took it, so he gave '
                                      'him Achsah his daughter as his wife.\n'
                                      'When she came, she got him to ask her '
                                      'father for a field. She got off her '
                                      "donkey; and Caleb said to her, 'What "
                                      "would you like?'\n"
                                      "She said to him, 'Give me a blessing; "
                                      'because you have set me in the land of '
                                      'the South, give me also springs of '
                                      "water.' Then Caleb gave her the upper "
                                      'springs and the lower springs.\n'
                                      "The children of the Kenite, Moses' "
                                      'brother-in-law, went up out of the city '
                                      'of palm trees with the children of '
                                      'Judah into the wilderness of Judah, '
                                      'which is in the south of Arad; and they '
                                      'went and lived with the people.\n'
                                      'Judah went with Simeon his brother, and '
                                      'they struck the Canaanites who '
                                      'inhabited Zephath, and utterly '
                                      'destroyed it. The name of the city was '
                                      'called Hormah.\n'
                                      'Also Judah took Gaza with its border, '
                                      'and Ashkelon with its border, and Ekron '
                                      'with its border.\n'
                                      'Yahweh was with Judah; and drove out '
                                      'the inhabitants of the hill country; '
                                      'for he could not drive out the '
                                      'inhabitants of the valley, because they '
                                      'had chariots of iron.\n'
                                      'They gave Hebron to Caleb, as Moses had '
                                      'said, and he drove the three sons of '
                                      'Anak out of there.\n'
                                      'The children of Benjamin did not drive '
                                      'out the Jebusites who inhabited '
                                      'Jerusalem, but the Jebusites dwell with '
                                      'the children of Benjamin in Jerusalem '
                                      'to this day.\n'
                                      'The house of Joseph also went up '
                                      'against Bethel, and Yahweh was with '
                                      'them.\n'
                                      'The house of Joseph sent to spy out '
                                      'Bethel. (The name of the city before '
                                      'that was Luz.)\n'
                                      'The watchers saw a man come out of the '
                                      "city, and they said to him, 'Please "
                                      'show us the entrance into the city, and '
                                      "we will deal kindly with you.'\n"
                                      'He showed them the entrance into the '
                                      'city, and they struck the city with the '
                                      'edge of the sword; but they let the man '
                                      'and all his family go.\n'
                                      'The man went into the land of the '
