                                      'inhabitants of Beth Shean and its '
                                      'towns, nor Taanach and its towns, nor '
                                      'the inhabitants of Dor and its towns, '
                                      'nor the inhabitants of Ibleam and its '
                                      'towns, nor the inhabitants of Megiddo '
                                      'and its towns; but the Canaanites would '
                                      'dwell in that land.\n'
                                      'When Israel had grown strong, they put '
                                      'the Canaanites to forced labor, and did '
                                      'not utterly drive them out.\n'
                                      "Ephraim didn't drive out the Canaanites "
                                      'who lived in Gezer, but the Canaanites '
                                      'lived in Gezer among them.\n'
