                                      'the hand of the house of Joseph '
                                      'prevailed, so that they became subject '
                                      'to forced labor.\n'
                                      'The border of the Amorites was from the '
                                      'ascent of Akrabbim, from the rock, and '
                                      'upward.\n'
                                      'Now the men of Israel had sworn in '
                                      "Mizpah, saying, 'None of us will give "
                                      "his daughter to Benjamin as a wife.'\n"
                                      'The people came to Bethel, and sat '
                                      'there until evening before God, and '
                                      'lifted up their voices, and wept '
                                      'severely.\n'
                                      "They said, 'Yahweh, the God of Israel, "
                                      'why has this happened in Israel, that '
                                      'there should be one tribe lacking in '
                                      "Israel today?'\n"
                                      'On the next day, the people rose early, '
                                      'and built an altar there, and offered '
                                      'burnt offerings and peace offerings.\n'
                                      "The children of Israel said, 'Who is "
                                      'there among all the tribes of Israel '
                                      "who didn't come up in the assembly to "
                                      "Yahweh?' For they had made a great oath "
                                      "concerning him who didn't come up to "
                                      "Yahweh to Mizpah, saying, 'He shall "
                                      "surely be put to death.'\n"
                                      'The children of Israel grieved for '
                                      'Benjamin their brother, and said, '
                                      "'There is one tribe cut off from Israel "
                                      'today.\n'
                                      'How shall we provide wives for those '
                                      'who remain, since we have sworn by '
                                      'Yahweh that we will not give them of '
                                      "our daughters to wives?'\n"
                                      "They said, 'What one is there of the "
                                      "tribes of Israel who didn't come up to "
                                      "Yahweh to Mizpah?' Behold, no one came "
                                      'from Jabesh Gilead to the camp to the '
                                      'assembly.\n'
                                      'For when the people were counted, '
                                      'behold, there were none of the '
                                      'inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead there.\n'
                                      'The congregation sent twelve thousand '
                                      'of the most valiant men there, and '
                                      "commanded them, saying, 'Go and strike "
                                      'the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead with '
                                      'the edge of the sword, with the women '
                                      'and the little ones.\n'
                                      'This is the thing that you shall do: '
                                      'you shall utterly destroy every male, '
                                      'and every woman who has lain with a '
                                      "man.'\n"
                                      'They found among the inhabitants of '
                                      'Jabesh Gilead four hundred young '
                                      'virgins, who had not known man by lying '
                                      'with him; and they brought them to the '
                                      'camp to Shiloh, which is in the land of '
                                      'Canaan.\n'
                                      'The whole congregation sent and spoke '
                                      'to the children of Benjamin who were in '
                                      'the rock of Rimmon, and proclaimed '
                                      'peace to them.\n'
                                      'Benjamin returned at that time; and '
                                      'they gave them the women whom they had '
                                      'saved alive of the women of Jabesh '
                                      "Gilead. There still weren't enough for "
                                      'them.\n'
                                      'The people grieved for Benjamin, '
                                      'because Yahweh had made a breach in the '
                                      'tribes of Israel.\n'
                                      'Then the elders of the congregation '
                                      "said, 'How shall we provide wives for "
                                      'those who remain, since the women are '
                                      "destroyed out of Benjamin?'\n"
                                      "They said, 'There must be an "
