                                       'years old and upward, all who were '
                                       'able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Reuben, were forty-six '
                                       'thousand five hundred.\n'
                                       'Of the children of Simeon, their '
                                       'generations, by their families, by '
                                       "their fathers' houses, those who were "
                                       'counted of it, according to the number '
                                       'of the names, one by one, every male '
                                       'from twenty years old and upward, all '
                                       'who were able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Simeon, were fifty-nine '
                                       'thousand three hundred.\n'
                                       'Of the children of Gad, their '
                                       'generations, by their families, by '
                                       "their fathers' houses, according to "
                                       'the number of the names, from twenty '
                                       'years old and upward, all who were '
                                       'able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Gad, were forty-five thousand '
                                       'six hundred fifty.\n'
                                       'Of the children of Judah, their '
                                       'generations, by their families, by '
                                       "their fathers' houses, according to "
                                       'the number of the names, from twenty '
                                       'years old and upward, all who were '
                                       'able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Judah, were seventy-four '
                                       'thousand six hundred.\n'
                                       'Of the children of Issachar, their '
                                       'generations, by their families, by '
                                       "their fathers' houses, according to "
                                       'the number of the names, from twenty '
                                       'years old and upward, all who were '
                                       'able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Issachar, were fifty-four '
