                                       'years old and upward, all who were '
                                       'able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Asher, were forty-one '
                                       'thousand five hundred.\n'
                                       'Of the children of Naphtali, their '
                                       'generations, by their families, by '
                                       "their fathers' houses, according to "
                                       'the number of the names, from twenty '
                                       'years old and upward, all who were '
                                       'able to go out to war;\n'
                                       'those who were counted of them, of the '
                                       'tribe of Naphtali, were fifty-three '
                                       'thousand four hundred.\n'
                                       'These are those who were counted, whom '
                                       'Moses and Aaron counted, and the '
                                       'princes of Israel, being twelve men: '
                                       "they were each one for his fathers' "
                                       'house.\n'
