                                         'your fathers.\n'
                                         'Therefore tell them: Yahweh of '
                                         "Armies says: 'Return to me,' says "
                                         "Yahweh of Armies, 'and I will return "
                                         "to you,' says Yahweh of Armies.\n"
                                         "Don't you be like your fathers, to "
                                         'whom the former prophets proclaimed, '
                                         'saying: Yahweh of Armies says, '
                                         "'Return now from your evil ways, and "
                                         "from your evil doings;' but they did "
                                         'not hear, nor listen to me, says '
                                         'Yahweh.\n'
                                         'Your fathers, where are they? And '
                                         'the prophets, do they live forever?\n'
                                         'But my words and my decrees, which I '
                                         'commanded my servants the prophets, '
                                         "didn't they overtake your fathers?\n"
                                         "'Then they repented and said, 'Just "
                                         'as Yahweh of Armies determined to do '
                                         'to us, according to our ways, and '
                                         'according to our practices, so he '
                                         "has dealt with us.''\n"
                                         'On the twenty-fourth day of the '
                                         'eleventh month, which is the month '
                                         'Shebat, in the second year of '
                                         "Darius, Yahweh's word came to "
                                         'Zechariah the son of Berechiah, the '
                                         'son of Iddo, the prophet, saying,\n'
                                         "'I had a vision in the night, and "
                                         'behold, a man riding on a red horse, '
                                         'and he stood among the myrtle trees '
                                         'that were in a ravine; and behind '
                                         'him there were red, brown, and white '
                                         'horses.\n'
                                         "Then I asked, 'My lord, what are "
                                         "these?''\n"
                                         'The angel who talked with me said to '
                                         "me, 'I will show you what these "
                                         "are.'\n"
                                         'The man who stood among the myrtle '
                                         "trees answered, 'They are the ones "
                                         'Yahweh has sent to go back and forth '
                                         "through the earth.'\n"
                                         "They reported to Yahweh's angel who "
                                         'stood among the myrtle trees, and '
                                         "said, 'We have walked back and forth "
                                         'through the earth, and behold, all '
                                         "the earth is at rest and in peace.'\n"
                                         "Then Yahweh's angel replied, 'O "
                                         'Yahweh of Armies, how long will you '
                                         'not have mercy on Jerusalem and on '
                                         'the cities of Judah, against which '
                                         'you have had indignation these '
                                         "seventy years?'\n"
